    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "it really is. it's like the person i was actually died when the data came back. there's nothing left to salvage. i'm just tired of pretending that there's some profound lesson to learn here. sometimes i think the only honest thing left to do is just... stop. is it really so wrong to think that when the purpose is gone, the presence shouldn't be either?",
